'''阿萨德家族'''（{{lang-ar|آل الأسد|d=asad|b=Löwe}}）自[[哈菲兹·阿萨德|哈菲兹·阿萨德]]于1970年發動{{le|校正革命|Corrective Movement (Syria)}}政變奪權成为总统后就一直統治[[叙利亚|叙利亚]]，至今。哈菲兹之子[[巴沙尔·阿萨德|巴沙尔·阿萨德]]于2000年父親逝世後继承总统至今<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.ou.edu/mideast/Additional%20pages%20-%20non-catagory/Zisser_al-Asad_and_his_Regime_2004.htm | title=Bashar al-Asad and his Regime - Between Continuity and Change | author=Eyal Zisser | year=2004 | publisher=Orient | accessdate=2011-04-02 | archive-date=2019-02-08 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190208125032/http://www.ou.edu/mideast/Additional%20pages%20-%20non-catagory/Zisser_al-Asad_and_his_Regime_2004.htm | dead-url=no }}</ref>。

家族发源地位于叙利亚西北部[[拉塔基亚|拉塔基亚]]港的[[卡爾達哈|卡爾達哈]]。他们是属于少数教派[[阿拉维派|阿拉维派]]的一个分支，隶属于卡尔比亚部落<ref name=PSeale9>{{cite book|last=McConville|first=Patrick Seale with the assistance of Maureen|title=Asad of Syria : The Struggle For The Middle East|year=1990|publisher=University of California Press|location=Berkeley|isbn=9780520069763|pages=9|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=6D9EiJKRTHcC&pg=PA9&dq=Kalbiya+seale&hl=en&ei=n1_hTuKaHuiE4gSOkriMBQ&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q&f=false}}</ref>。家族可以追溯到阿里·蘇萊曼（1875－1963年），他于1927年將姓氏改为阿萨德（Al Assad，阿拉伯语中的意思是“[[狮子|狮子]]”）。目前所有的家族成员都是阿里·苏莱曼及其二房妻子娜伊莎（她出自安努萨里耶山脉地区的一个阿拉维派家庭）的后代<ref name="Stäheli">Martin Stäheli: ''Die syrische Außenpolitik unter Hafiz Assad'', Franz Steiner Verlag, Stuttgart 2001, ISBN 3-515-07867-3; S. 40</ref>。

该家族人士自从哈菲兹因為{{le|校正革命|Corrective Movement (Syria)}}而上台以来，一直到现在都控制着叙利亚党政军的各方面权力而进行着专制獨裁统治<ref>{{cite news|title=Sanctions on Businessman Target Syria's Inner Sanctum|author=Robin Wright|newspaper=The Washington Post|date=February 22, 2008|url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2008/02/21/AR2008022102839.html|accessdate=March 31, 2010|archive-date=2018-10-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181004071356/http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2008/02/21/AR2008022102839.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=Bar_S.380>{{cite journal|last=Bar|first=Shmuel|title=Bashar's Syria: The Regime and its Strategic Worldview|journal=Comparative Strategy|year=2006|volume=25|pages=380|url=http://www.herzliyaconference.org/_Uploads/2590Bashars.pdf|accessdate=15 May 2011|archive-date=2011-07-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110723214138/http://www.herzliyaconference.org/_Uploads/2590Bashars.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

